beneficiary_eligability:
Veterans who meet basic VA eligibility requirement for VA healthcare and who are assessed as: 
not meeting criteria for acute inpatient mental health or medical admission; 
having tried a less restrictive treatment alternative, or one was unavailable; 
having identified rehabilitation and treatment needs requiring the structure and support of a residential treatment environment; 
not a significant risk of harm to self or others; 
lacking a stable lifestyle or living arrangement that is conducive to the Veteran’s goal of recovery; 
being capable of self-preservation and basic self-care.
